# Build context for all images under tests/Dockerfiles/ is now this directory.
# Without this filter, every `docker build` would tar-stream the Node test
# harness and all of node_modules/ to the daemon — easily 100s of MB. The
# Dockerfiles only need the small helper files inside per-test subfolders
# (entrypoint.sh, *.conf, *.cnf, the nrdp/nsca/nrpe test data folders).

# Node / TypeScript harness — never needed in any image.
node_modules/
src/

# Root-level files that belong to the test runner, not any image.
package.json
package-lock.json
tsconfig.json
jest.config.js
acceptance-tests.bat
acceptance-tests.sh
run-all-tests.bat

# Jest test sources. The Dockerfiles never reference these.
**/*.test.ts

# Legacy per-folder batch runners (kept on disk for documentation; not built
# into images).
**/run-test.bat
**/run-test-cmk-site.bat

# README and design docs.
README.md

# Editor / OS cruft.
.DS_Store
Thumbs.db
*.log
